{
  "text": "Besides DNA methylation, histone modifications and chromatin remodeling also play important roles in epigenetic regulation of gene expression. For instance, trimethylation of Histone H3 lysine 4 (H3K4me3) is associated with gene activation, whereas trimethylation of Histone H3 lysine 27 (H3K27me3) marks repressed genes. Plant SET-domain genes (SDG) are involved in histone methylation that can be removed by specific histone demethylases such as Jumonji (JMJ)-C domain containing proteins identified in rice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
